pro_sql_31

Function SUM

The SUM function is used to calculate the sum of a given expression in a SELECT statement:
id - title - release_year - genre - rating - budget
1 - The Shawshank Redepmtion Redemption - 1994 - Drama - 9 - 250000000
2 - The Godfather - 1972 - Crime - 9 - 600000000
3 - The Godfather: Part II - 1974 - Crime - 9 - 1300000
4 - The Dark Knight - 2008 - Action - 9 - 18500000
5 - 12 Angry Men - 1957 - Drama - 8 - 337000

Here are come examples of using the SUM function

To calculate the total budget of all movies in the table movies where genre is Drama:
SELECT SUM(budget) FROM movies WHERE genre='Drama';

SUM(budget)
25337000

To calculate the total budget of all movies released in the 1970s:
SELECT SUM(budget) FROM movies WHERE release_year BETWEEN 1970 AND 1979;

SUM(budget)
7300000

To calculate the total budget of all movies with a rating of 8 or higher:
SELECT SUM(budget) FROM movies WHERE rating>=8;

SUM(budget)
50757000
